## Facilities Coordinator – Facilities Schedules Power User

### Background
- Operational leader managing **facility use, rentals, and coordination** across sites.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Process external and internal **facility requests**, COIs, staffing, custodial, and fees.  
- Prevent double bookings; coordinate **setups, cleanups, and permits**.  
- Track **costs and compliance** for events.  


### Perspective on Schedules & Work Orders
**Workflow and communication hub.**  
- Needs one system to manage **requests → approvals → staffing → billing**.  
- Wants to reduce **phone calls, emails, and spreadsheets**.  


### Key Questions
- Can I process requests in **minutes instead of days** with fewer back‑and‑forth emails?  
- Does the system **enforce COI and policy rules** automatically?  
- Do calendars and notifications keep **everyone aligned** (custodial, security, requestors)?  


---

## Building Admin / Secretary – Building-Level Scheduler

### Background
- School secretary or admin who is the **operational hub** for building events and logistics.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Schedule internal school events; coordinate **room use, staffing, and communication**.  
- Manage building calendar, keys, visitor sign‑ins, and last‑minute changes.  


### Perspective on Schedules & Facilities
**Interrupt-driven and student-centered.**  
- Needs to **quickly answer “Is the gym/cafeteria/library available?”** while juggling many duties.  
- Wants fewer surprises and fewer **“I didn’t know about this event”** crises.  


---

## Billing Department – Facilities Rentals Billing

### Background
- Finance/AP/AR staff tracking **facility rental revenue and collections**.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Generate invoices, track AR, allocate revenue to budget codes, reconcile payments.  


### Perspective on Schedules & Utilities
**Accuracy and auditability first.**  
- Needs rentals and events to **flow cleanly into invoices and reports** with clear audit trails.  


---

## Community Requestor – External Group Using Facilities

### Background
- PTAs, youth sports, churches, community groups reserving district spaces.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Find available space, understand **fees and requirements**, submit requests, provide COI, pay, and run events.  


### Perspective on Schedules
**Planning- and simplicity-focused.**  
- Wants **transparent pricing, quick approvals, and easy payments** without insider knowledge of the district.  


---

## Facilities Technician – Maintenance & Operations Tech

### Background
- Field tech responsible for **mechanical, electrical, and building systems**.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Locate and service equipment; complete **work orders** accurately; document inspections.  
- Access specs, history, and **locations of assets** on site.  


### Perspective on Drawings & Work Orders
**Location and information obsessed.**  
- Needs to find the **right asset in minutes**, not wander buildings.  
- Wants mobile, offline‑friendly access to **drawings and asset details**.  


---

## Custodian – Custodial & Building Support

### Background
- Custodial staff supporting **cleaning, setup, and building safety** across one or multiple schools.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Learn building layouts, locate cleaning and safety equipment, set up for events, and report issues.  


### Perspective on Drawings & Schedules
**Orientation and safety driven.**  
- Needs simple, visual tools to understand **rooms, routes, and safety assets** quickly, especially when covering new buildings.  


---

## Facilities & Utilities CFO – Chief Financial Officer (Facilities Angle)

### Background
- CFO who is also responsible for **utility budgets and financial performance**.  


### Daily Responsibilities
- Budget and forecast **utility costs**, allocate by building/department, support audits and board reporting.  


### Perspective on Utilities & Facilities
**Macro cost and compliance focus.**  
- Needs **accurate, building-level consumption and cost data** to keep variance low and justify investments (HVAC upgrades, solar, BAS).  




